    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The size difference is due to different load. Geth pushes state to disk stuff after every hour of processing, if your node is more loaded, it can process less blocks in 1h, so it pushes to disk more frequently. We're working on some way to prune in the future, but there are some database migration steps involved first.",
